      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/t12-24.2",
      "@type": [
        "isoiec80000:Quantity",
        "smart:TermEntry"
      ],
      "dcterms:identifier": "12-24.2",
      "skosxl:prefLabel": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/term-t12-24.2-0"
      },
      "skosxl:altLabel": [
        {
          "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/sym-t12-24.2-0"
        }
      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "difference between energy (<<iso80000-5>>) of an electron at rest at infinity and a certain energy level which is the energy of an electron in the interior of a substance",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "The term \"energy level\" is often used for the state of the electron, not only for its energy.\n\nThe contact potential difference between substances a and b is given by\n\n[stem%unnumbered]\n++++\nV_\"a\" - V_\"b\" = (phi_\"a\"-phi_\"b\")/e\n++++\n\nwhere stem:[e] is the elementary charge (<<iso80000-1>>).\n\nA set of energy levels, the energies of which occupy an interval practically continuously, is called an energy band.\n\nIn semi-conductors stem:[E_\"d\"] and stem:[E_\"a\"] are used for donors and acceptors, respectively.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-J"
        },
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-eV"
        },
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^2*s^(-2)"
        }
      ],
      "smart:hasBindingnessType": {
        "@id": "smart:normative"
      },
      "dcterms:isPartOf": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/standards/isoiec80000/ontologies/core/part-12"
      }
    }
  ]
